<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="414" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d414">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">500.CC/8–1144</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Soviet Chargé</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Kapustin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-08-11">August 11,
                                1944</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Mr. Secretary</hi>: Referring to my letter
                            of July 24<note n="72" xml:id="d414fn72">Not printed.</note> I have the
                            honor to inform you additionally of the full composition of the
                            delegation of the U.S.S.R., appointed by the Government of the U.S.S.R.
                            for participation in the forthcoming informal discussions on the
                            questions of establishment of an international organization of
                            security.</p>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">Chairman of the Delegation</hi>, Andrei
                                Andreyevich Gromyko<note n="73" xml:id="d414fn73">Ambassador in the
                                    United States.</note>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">Deputy-Chairman</hi>, Arkadi Alexandrovich
                                    Sobolev<note n="74" xml:id="d414fn74">Minister Counselor of
                                    Embassy in the United Kingdom.</note>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">Members of the Delegation:</hi>
                                <list>
                                    <item>Semen Konstantinovich Zarapkin<note n="75" xml:id="d414fn75">Chief of the American section of the
                                            Soviet Foreign Office.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>Maj. General Nikolai Vassilievich Slavin<note n="76" xml:id="d414fn76">Member of the Soviet General
                                            Staff.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>Rear Admiral Konstantin Konstantinovich Rodionov<note n="77" xml:id="d414fn77">Chief of the Administrative
                                            Division of the Navy Commissariat.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>Professor Sergei Alexandrovich Golunsky</item>
                                    <item>Professor Sergei Borisovich Krylov<note n="78" xml:id="d414fn78">Member of the Foreign Office.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <item>Grigori Georgievich Dolbin<note n="79" xml:id="d414fn79">Professor of international law at Moscow
                                            University.</note>
                                    </item>
                                </list>
                            </item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary of the Delegation</hi>, Mikhail
                                Mikhailovich Yunin</item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="italic">Secretary-interpreter</hi>, Valentin Mikhailovich
                                    Berezhkov<note n="80" xml:id="d414fn80">Counselor, Soviet
                                    Foreign Office. <p>Press Officer Feodor T. Orekhov was also
                                        included in the personnel list in <hi rend="italic">Postwar
                                            Foreign Policy Preparation</hi>, p. 304.</p>
                                </note>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                        <p>Sincerely yours,</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>A. <hi rend="smallcaps">Kapustin</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>